<span id="freeTextContainer6479650633296672419">As a first book by the author it is an impressive work. The way the book has been written is good and keeps you well engaged. The book tries to balance mythology and science which is done well and you can actually see science connecting to mythology. For those who have a very basic understanding of mythology this book will make your help you develop a rational attitude towards understanding mythology. Author has done his background work really well and it becomes evident by the depth he reaches </span>
  <span id="freeText6479650633296672419" style="display:none">As a first book by the author it is an impressive work. The way the book has been written is good and keeps you well engaged. The book tries to balance mythology and science which is done well and you can actually see science connecting to mythology. For those who have a very basic understanding of mythology this book will make your help you develop a rational attitude towards understanding mythology. Author has done his background work really well and it becomes evident by the depth he reaches in explaining things. The book has used some innovative concepts like replacing chapters with adhyays which are well connected and have a smooth flow. Also the way message is well conveyed. Hence, I can say "Do read it once". <br /></span>
