        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2028088897" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1265589426772420737">Dr. Vineet Aggarwal did a good job with his debut &apos;Vishwamitra&apos;. It a simple read and the research done by the author is visible. The tale of Rishi Vishwamitra is told is such a way that the reader is hooked to the book. It is the story of Vishwartha and his transformation to Vishwamitra. The story begins with Satyavati, her marriage and birth of Yamadagni &amp; Vishwartha. The author talks in detail about the encounters between Vasishta and Vishwartha. For me, these encounters were the most interes</span>
  <span id="freeText1265589426772420737" style="display:none">Dr. Vineet Aggarwal did a good job with his debut 'Vishwamitra'. It a simple read and the research done by the author is visible. The tale of Rishi Vishwamitra is told is such a way that the reader is hooked to the book. It is the story of Vishwartha and his transformation to Vishwamitra. The story begins with Satyavati, her marriage and birth of Yamadagni &amp; Vishwartha. The author talks in detail about the encounters between Vasishta and Vishwartha. For me, these encounters were the most interesting parts of the book.<br /><br />I would recommend this book to anyone interested in philosophy, mythology.</span>
